                "display_name": "gusto2",
                "accept_rate": 73
            },
            "content_license": "CC BY-SA 3.0",
            "score": 0,
            "is_accepted": false,
            "last_activity_date": 1500975018,
            "creation_date": 1500975018,
            "body": "<p>Information you have is very obsolete. What you describe was valid for OS when each process was effectviely a single thread (Windows 3.1, or OLD unix kernels, Macintosh system 7). That time JVM running as a single process had to implement its own thread scheduler and thread management.<\/p>\n\n<p>Today all common platforms support natively multithreading and by default JVM uses the underlying system implementation<\/p>\n",
            "answer_id": 45299235,
            "question_id": 45298026
        }
